text.section:
To enforce this title the Secretary may adopt regulations relating to:
Standards of net weight, measure, or count, reasonable standards of fill, and labeling requirements, for any commodity in package form;
Exemptions from the sealing or marking requirements of § 11-207 of this subtitle with respect to weights and measures whose character or size makes sealing or marking inappropriate, not feasible, or damaging to the weight and measure;
Registration of servicemen and service agencies engaged in the maintenance and repair of weighing and measuring devices;
The types of commodities and objects to be weighed by licensed weighmasters; and
The types of weighing devices requiring operation by a licensed weighmaster, the licensing of weighmasters and applicants' licensing fees, the maintenance of weight records, and inspection of weight records by the Secretary.
